description:
From Dusk till Dawn: The Series is an American horror television series developed by Robert Rodriguez. It forms part of the franchise of film, direct-to-video, comic and cult following of From Dusk till Dawn, expanding on the chronicles of the Gecko Brothers, Seth and Richie; The Fuller family; and Santanico Pandemonium.[1] The series premiered on March 11, 2014,[2][3] on Rodriguez's newly launched channel El Rey.[4] Outside the United States and Latin America, the series is marketed as a Netflix original.

It is being produced by FactoryMade Ventures in association with Miramax and executive produced by Rodriguez.

The series adds to the tone of the film, with new characters and backstories, while expanding the creatures' Mesoamerican mythology.
